Linux Command Line Foundations
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Navigate the Linux file system using essential directory commands
Understand the Linux directory structure and current working directory concept
Perform basic file management operations including copying, moving, and deleting files
Create and edit text files using both vim and nano text editors
Apply proper command syntax and understand command options
Demonstrate proficiency with fundamental Linux terminal operations
Prerequisites
Before starting this lab, students should have:

Basic understanding of what an operating system is
Familiarity with the concept of files and folders
No prior Linux experience required - this lab starts from the beginning
Ability to type commands accurately
